    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Micah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 6,
        "summary": "In spite of all His goodness to them, the people have not served the Lord in spirit and in truth\u2014They must act righteously, love mercy, and walk humbly before Him.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Hear ye now what the Lord saith; Arise, contend thou before the mountains, and let the hills hear thy voice.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear ye, O mountains, the Lord's controversy, and ye strong foundations of the earth: for the Lord hath a controversy with his people, and he will plead with Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 4:1.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 3:13 (12\u201313).",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O my people, what have I done unto thee? and wherein have I wearied thee? testify against me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I brought thee up out of the land of Egypt, and redeemed thee out of the house of servants; and I sent before thee Moses, Aaron, and Miriam.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 7:13 (11\u201313); Alma 29:12.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O my people, remember now what Balak king of Moab consulted, and what Balaam the son of Beor answered him from Shittim unto Gilgal; that ye may know the righteousness of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 22:2 (2\u20135).",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1155
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherewith shall I come before the Lord, and bow myself before the high God? shall I come before him with burnt offerings, with calves of a year old?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Will the Lord be pleased with thousands of rams, or with ten thousands of rivers of oil? shall I give my firstborn for my transgression, the fruit of my body for the sin of my soul?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 15:22; Heb. 10:6 (4\u20136).",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Firstborn.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He hath shewed thee, O man, what is good; and what doth the Lord require of thee, but to do justly, and to love mercy, and to walk humbly with thy God?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 64:34 (22, 34). TG\u00a0Duty; God, the Standard of Righteousness.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works; Justice.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mercy.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 130
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children of Light; Humility.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord's voice crieth unto the city, and the man of wisdom shall see thy name: hear ye the rod, and who hath appointed it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Are there yet the treasures of wickedness in the house of the wicked, and the scant measure that is abominable?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Shall I count them pure with the wicked balances, and with the bag of deceitful weights?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 34:7.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 12:7.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the rich men thereof are full of violence, and the inhabitants thereof have spoken lies, and their tongue is deceitful in their mouth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hab. 1:2.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore also will I make thee sick in smiting thee, in making thee desolate because of thy sins.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt eat, but not be satisfied; and thy casting down shall be in the midst of thee; and thou shalt take hold, but shalt not deliver; and that which thou deliverest will I give up to the sword.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 26:26.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0thy hunger shall be in thy inward parts.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 143,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt sow, but thou shalt not reap; thou shalt tread the olives, but thou shalt not anoint thee with oil; and sweet wine, but shalt not drink wine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:38; Hag. 1:6.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the statutes of Omri are kept, and all the works of the house of Ahab, and ye walk in their counsels; that I should make thee a desolation, and the inhabitants thereof an hissing: therefore ye shall bear the reproach of my people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 16:25 (16, 25\u201326).",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 18:16 (16\u201317); 24:10.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 142
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 24:9; 2\u00a0Ne. 29:5.",
                        "start": 212,
                        "end": 220
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
